Yeah, I didn't look to closely to figure out where the empty path exception comes from, but I feel like it comes from Modeshape. I was able to perform the matching with this
    private boolean hasEmptyPathSegments(final HttpServletRequest httpRequest) {
        final String requestPath = httpRequest.getContextPath() + httpRequest.getServletPath() +
                httpRequest.getRequestURI();
        final String finalTestPath;
        if (requestPath.startsWith("/") && requestPath.endsWith("/") && requestPath.length() > 1) {
            finalTestPath = requestPath.substring(1, requestPath.length() - 2);
        } else if (requestPath.startsWith("/")) {
            finalTestPath = requestPath.substring(1);
        } else if (requestPath.endsWith("/")) {
            finalTestPath = requestPath.substring(0, requestPath.length() - 1);
        } else {
            finalTestPath = requestPath;
        }
        if (finalTestPath.contains("/")) {
            final String[] paths = finalTestPath.split("/");
            if (Arrays.stream(paths).anyMatch(String::isEmpty)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

I'm not sure how fragile that is, but if you want I can add a commit here to return the appropriate 400 Bad Request. I'd probably add more test cases here than in the 6.0.0 location.
